wikipedia_page.main: Diana White (19 June 1868  - 21 January 1950) was a British artist and translator.  She painted Impressionist-style landscapes and translated, into English, books authored in French and Danish.  Her most sought-after work is the 1903 book The Descent of Ishtar of which only 226 copies were printed.
